A Guide to the Rockefeller University records, Catalogs and Directories FA207

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on 2019-11-01 01:33:31 -0400.

did.unittitle: Rockefeller University records, Catalogs and Directories

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Boxes 1-5 were received from Mary Galgan, RU Library, December 1984. Accretions received as transferred.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Level 1 Minimal Processing has been conducted to establish basic intellectual and physical control of the material and assess immediate preservation and conservation needs. Material remains as received, in original record storage cartons.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Material is primarily arranged as received.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Open for research. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Types of records include: financial summaries, directories, catalogues, reviews, and reports.
